headline: EME Q1 Earnings Call: Data Center and Healthcare Expansion Drive Outperformance, Tariff Risks Managed
summary: Specialty construction contractor company EMCOR (NYSE:EME) reported Q1 CY2025 results exceeding the market’s revenue expectations, with sales up 12.7% year on year to $3.87 billion. The company’s full-year revenue guidance of $16.5 billion at the midpoint came in 0.8% above analysts’ estimates. Its non-GAAP profit of $5.26 per share was 13.7% above analysts’ consensus estimates.
